@startuml workspace-switch-token-refresh
title Workspace Switch and Token Refresh

hide footbox

skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam defaultFontSize 16
skinparam sequence {
  ArrowColor #111111
  LifeLineBorderColor #111111
  LifeLineBackgroundColor #FFFFFF
  ParticipantBorderColor #111111
  ParticipantBackgroundColor #FFFFFF
  ParticipantFontColor #111111
  ParticipantFontSize 16
  ActorBorderColor #111111
  ActorBackgroundColor #FFFFFF
  ActorFontSize 16
  GroupBorderColor #111111
  GroupBackgroundColor #FFFFFF
}

actor "Workspace User" as User
participant "App UI" as UI
participant "Routes +\nValidation" as Routes
participant "Auth + User\nGuards" as Guards
participant "Workspace\nController" as WorkspaceController
participant "Workspace\nService" as WorkspaceService
participant "Auth\nController" as AuthController
participant "Auth\nService" as AuthService
participant "Session/Token\nService" as SessionService
participant "Domain Models\nUser/Session/Workspace/Member" as Models
participant "Realtime\nRuntime" as Realtime

== 1. Request workspace switch ==

User -> UI: Select target workspace
UI -> Routes: POST /api/workspaces/switch
Routes -> Guards: requireAuth + active user
Routes -> WorkspaceController: validated workspaceId
WorkspaceController -> WorkspaceService: switchWorkspaceForSession(user, session, workspace)

== 2. Validate membership and workspace ==

WorkspaceService -> Models: find target workspace
WorkspaceService -> Models: verify active membership\nand role in target workspace

== 3. Update session workspace ==

WorkspaceService -> Models: update Session.workspaceId
WorkspaceService -> Models: update User.lastWorkspaceId

== 4. Mint replacement access token ==

WorkspaceService -> SessionService: mintAccessTokenForSession(new workspace, role)
SessionService -> Models: verify session is active
SessionService --> WorkspaceService: replacement access token
WorkspaceService -> Realtime: disconnect sockets for session
WorkspaceService --> UI: switched workspace + role + accessToken

== 5. Refresh uses session workspace ==

UI -> Routes: POST /api/auth/refresh
Routes -> AuthController: validated refreshToken
AuthController -> AuthService: refresh(refreshToken)
AuthService -> SessionService: validate refresh token and session hash
SessionService -> Models: load active session\nwith current workspaceId
AuthService -> WorkspaceService: resolve active workspace context\nfrom session.workspaceId
WorkspaceService -> Models: verify active workspace + membership
AuthService -> SessionService: rotate refresh/access tokens
SessionService -> Models: update refreshTokenHash\nand keep session workspace
AuthService --> UI: refreshed accessToken + refreshToken

@enduml
